<h3 class="mb-3">Tags</h3>

<p><em>Tag</em> your lessons any way you like but it's good practice to tag with as many concepts covered in the lesson as possible.

<p class='mb-0'><em>Tags</em> will appear:-</p>
<ul>
	<li>In the content of the <em>Lesson</em> page</li>
	<li>In the footer of every page (desktop and tablet only)</li>
</ul>

<div class="d-flex my-2">
	<div style="width: 30%;" class="mr-5">
		<%= help_image_tag('tags-footer', '100%') %>
		<p class="admin_help_caption" style="width: 100%;">This screenshot shows the list of <em>Tags</em> at the footer of each page  (desktop and tablet only).</p>
	</div>

	<div style="width: 30%;">
		<%= help_image_tag('tags-sidebar', '100%') %>
		<p class="admin_help_caption" style="width: 100%;">This screenshot shows the list of <em>Tags</em> on the lesson page (dark) along with the list of <em>Categories</em> (light).</p>
	</div>
</div>

<p>Students can click on the tag to view all <em>Lessons</em> that share the same tag. And the resulting list of lessons can again be filtered down by <em>Category</em></p>

<%= help_image_tag('tags-results', '45%') %>
<p class="admin_help_caption" style="width: 45%;">This shows the <em>Lessons</em> tagged as 'practicing' and then filtered down by the 'co-Ordination' <em>Category</em></p>
